owPublicProfile?language=EN>Symphonie Orchestra</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/01 6:41:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Taunting  Part 2, Enchanted Mobs</span><hr size=1> What in your opinion is the best method for taunting off enchanted mobs from attacking the Enchanter? I know this sounds basic but sometimes I have actually had mezed mobs that I taunted attack the Chanter immeadiatly after I taunted. Am I doing something wrong? <p>Symphonie Orchestra
<BR>51 Gnome Warrior
<BR>The Valkyries of Norrath(Eci)
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utaluracwnzeylon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talura cwnZeylon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/01 10:29:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunting  Part 2, Enchanted Mobs</span><hr size=1> Best method? Root 'em. It's a good job for the pallies in the group to do, since they cannot seem to find anything better for their mana.<br>
But that aside, have the cleric ready with either a root or atone for right after they cast a heal on the chanter...then melee gets up close and lets the poor sucker know exactly why it shouldn't be beating up on dress-wearing weaklings. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ujoaquinarmillaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Joaquin Armillaria</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif  BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/01 11:08:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunting  Part 2, Enchanted Mobs</span><hr size=1> If you have a druid or a ranger make SURE they snare or try to snare every single add during the fight...  This will slow them down so you dont have a full speed mob chasing anyone, enchie or druid ( I am one but I know and HATE the ones that run screaming like girlies cuz they are getting it a bit...)  Also the druid/ranger has the hps to take a couple hits waiting for either the ench to re-mez or the tank to taunt it off...  Another thing is get the ench to memblur if they can...  This will help you out a bit as well. <p><p align="left" style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 5"><font face="Lucida Sans" color="#00FF00">Ctair Devernius, Druidic Priest of the 40th circle</font></p>
<p align="left" style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 5"><a href="http://pub49.ezboard.com/bstormlegion29646"><font face="Lucida Sans" size="6" color="#FF0000">Storm Legion</font></a></p>
<p align="left" style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 5"><b><font color="#000000" size="1">"Our task must be to free
ourselves from the prison by widening our circle of compassion to embrace all
living creatures and the whole of nature in its beauty..." - Albert Einstein
</font></b><font color="#000000" size="1"><br>
</font></p>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaerildroigheann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/01 11:59:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunting  Part 2, Enchanted Mobs</span><hr size=1> The way I do it is put 1 taunt in while the mob is mezed.  When taunt is available again turn on attack and taunt right after you break mez.  It works most of the time, but there are always going to be times when it doesn't like if taunt fails or if the mob has been mezed for a long time or debuffed a lot, etc. <p>~Tunare's Enforcer~<br>
<a href="http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=4080">Aeril Droigheann</a>, 59 Preserver<br>
<a href="http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=4050">Aeryl Firebrand</a>, Warlord<br>
Aerul Cuinnsear, 43 Rogue<br>
Undaunted, Xegony<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uraaj.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raaj</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.screamdesign.com/graphics/webgraphics/free/other/bullets/u104.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/01 12:04:35 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://raajgnomepunter.tripod.com/Personal.jpg border=0 width=100 height=175></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunting  Part 2, Enchanted Mobs</span><hr size=1> Depends<br>
<br>
<br>
Usually I will kick, if the kick lands it stuns, then i attack/taunt/disarm at once.<br>
<br>
If the kick doesnt land, mob still is mezzed and you taunt/disarm/attack. <p><hr>
<br>
<p>
<img src="http://raajgnomepunter.tripod.com/sig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubearogfrostborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bearog Frostborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/01 12:16:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunting  Part 2, Enchanted Mobs</span><hr size=1> Usually I take a once a week trip to CC and stock up on silken nets, 2 charges of ensnaring roots.<br>
I taunt twice and cast root, then slam attack, usually I hit slam first in an effort to stun. I will on occasion break the mez like this but using a weighted axe, doing usually 150 150 or better, in general it seems that much damage is enough to get it stuck back on me.  I switch weapons back quickly while a hybrid or another warrior continues to beat on it etc.  <br>
I am not sure if it is my imagination or not, but it seems to me that the Kunzar is procing more and more often as I level.  It has been procing on the first hit or so.  Has anyone ever noticed a correlation between when a weapon procs at X level and if it procs more often in later levels?<br>
<br>
My 2 coins.<br>
<br>
Bear <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugreblaja.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Greblaja</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/25/01 12:35:27 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunting  Part 2, Enchanted Mobs</span><hr size=1> If time permits, I throw 2-3 taunts before breaking mez.  <br>
