<br>
i find the following:<br>
<br>
clerics shouldnt waste a slot on atone, my mem blur is better (and yes its always memed in heavy CC situation)<br>
<br>
paldins should root and stun<br>
<br>
2 taunts is plenty <p>Aldarion/Azeroeth</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uddarkreaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ddarkreaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/29/01 9:09:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://208.162.125.24/eq/family/images/heads/darias_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Taunting  Part 2, Enchanted Mobs</span><hr size=1> Most of the time, I'm too lazy to use this method, but if you want to be absolutely certain the mob isn't going to beat on one of the casters when you break mez, after taunting, /assist with the mob targeted.  If your current target after doing this is a caster, repeat until that is not the case.<br>
